    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Aakash Educational Services South Asia Partners. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Senior Teacher to strengthen our Bengaluru-based team.\n\nAbout Aakash Educational Services South Asia Partners:\nAakash Educational Services South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Participate in teacher training and professional development programs\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n• Contribute to school newsletter, blogs, and other publications\n• Conduct doubt-clearing sessions and remedial classes for weak students\n• Maintain classroom discipline and create a positive learning environment\n• Design formative and summative assessments aligned to learning objectives\n• Support students with special educational needs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n• Proficiency in Child Psychology\n• Proficiency in CBSE/ICSE Standards\n• Proficiency in Data Analysis\n• Proficiency in Classroom Management\n• Proficiency in Research Skills\n• Proficiency in Student Assessment\n• Proficiency in Pedagogy\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Referral bonus program\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Flexible working hours\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Aakash Educational Services South Asia Partners!",
